title: SpaceX begins 2023 with Transporter-6 launch
summary: After a record-setting year of launch activity in 2022, SpaceX kicked off the new year Jan. 3 with a Falcon 9 launch of more than 110 smallsats.

title: After doubling launch record in 2022, can SpaceX take another step up in 2023?
summary: The company may aim for as many as 100 launches in 2023.

title: NASA planetary science budget remains under stress
summary: Despite a small funding increase for 2023, NASA’s planetary science programs still face “significant stress” financially that contributed to the delay of one mission and could push back the start of others.

title: SpaceX rings in 2023 with Transporter-6 rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX began another busy year with the launch of the Transporter-6 rideshare mission from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station (CCSFS). The mission lifted off at 9:56 AM EST (14:56 UTC) on Tuesday, Jan. 3, 2023. Falcon 9’s first stage returned to land at Landing Zone-1 at CCSFS approximately eight and a half minutes after launch.

title: Space solar power experiment, 36 Planet imaging satellites on SpaceX rideshare mission
summary: The 114 small satellites set for launch Tuesday on SpaceX’s first mission of the year include 36 spacecraft for Planet’s commercial remote sensing fleet, a space-based solar power experiment, and space tugs to piggyback payloads into different orbits.

title: Military officials forecast 87 launches from Florida’s Space Coast in 2023
summary: The U.S. Space Force is preparing for as many as 87 launches from Florida’s Space Coast in 2023, including dozens more SpaceX missions and the expected debuts of United Launch Alliance’s Vulcan and Relativity’s Terran 1 rockets.

title: Revenue shortfall causes layoffs and delays at Satellogic
summary: As Satellogic prepares to launch its latest imaging satellites, the company has slashed revenue projections, resulting in layoffs and delays in construction of a new factory.

title: SpaceX will try to follow record-breaking 2022 with busier 2023
summary: SpaceX has shattered the record for launches in a calendar year by a single rocket type while making large strides toward getting the successor vehicle off the ground, despite a few struggles with Falcon 9 launch delays and Starship testing mishaps.
